## Idea

The generalization of a $G$-[[principal âˆž-bundle]] over an [[âˆž-group]] $G$ as $G$ is generalized to a [[groupoid object in an (âˆž,1)-category]].

## Definition

For $\mathbf{H}$ an [[(âˆž,1)-topos]] and $\mathbf{G}_\bullet \in Grp_\infty(\mathbf{H})$ a [[groupoid object in an (âˆž,1)-category]], a **$\mathcal{G}_\bullet$-principal $\infty$-bundle** over $X$ is

* a morphism $P \to X$

* equipped with an anchor $a \colon P \to \mathcal{G}_0$ and a [[groupoid âˆž-action]] of $\mathcal{G}_\bullet$ on $(P,a)$ over $X$;

* such that $P \to X \simeq (P//\mathcal{G})$ is the corresponding quotient map.

